"a.潇洒的；放荡的 【英】 adj. 潇洒的, 放荡的(jaunty; stylish; sporty; dissolute) adj. 放荡的(具有性生活放纵的特点的) 【记】ra = re反复, kish读: 开始, 反复的开始 ＃￥％－放荡的 【类】rakish: restraint = slothful: assiduity放荡的不会抑制 = 偷懒的不会刻苦 【记】rake 耙子，猪八戒的东西，天篷元帅，潇洒却好色放荡，被贬到下界为猪 rakish (adj.)  1706, ""debauched, disreputable,"" from rake (n.2) + -ish. Related: Rakishly; rakishness. The meaning ""smart, jaunty, dashing"" (1824) is said to be a different word, probably from rake ""slant, slope"" (1620s), used especially in reference to a ship's hull or sails, of uncertain origin, perhaps from Scandinavian (compare Old Swedish raka ""project, reach;"" Danish rage ""protrude, project"") related to Old English reccan ""stretch."" ""The piratical craft of former times were distinguished for their rakish build"" [Century Dictionary]."
